article.description: — A.J. Walker scored 23 points and Air Force won its seventh consecutive game, defeating Army 76-58 on Saturday.
article.headline: Walker scores 23 to lead Air Force past Army 76-58
article.linkText: Walker scores 23 to lead Air Force past Army 76-58
article.story: COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. -- — A.J. Walker scored 23 points and Air Force won its seventh consecutive game, defeating Army 76-58 on Saturday. Air Force never trailed as it built a 9-0 lead and extended the margin to 32-8 with 7:38 before halftime. Walker scored seven straight during a 23-0 run and the Falcons led 45-13 at halftime. Ethan Taylor added 15 points, eight rebounds and eight assists for Air Force (7-1). Jalen Rucker scored 17 points for the Black Knights (4-4) and Aaron Duhart 11. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ Elements of this were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
